									 Honors 

  Life-time  Docent  title awarded by the Rector of University of Turku, Finland, 2016.  
  Global Marie Curie Fellowship  awarded by the  European Union (EU)</strong> with the score of 94.5% (success rate EU-wide 
  Nominee for  "The Teacher of the Year"</strong> at University of Turku, chosen by students (university-wide), 2016. 
  Rank 10</strong> by number of publications at University of Turku (among  544</strong> authors  in the field of engineering</strong>) over the period 2011 to 2015, according to  Elsevier SciVal</strong>. 
  Rank 10</strong> by number of publications at University of Turku (among  544</strong> authors  in the field of computer science</strong>) over the period 2011 to 2015, according to  Elsevier SciVal</strong>. 
  Rank 52</strong> by number of publications at University of Turku (among  4893</strong> authors  in all subject areas</strong>) over the period 2011 to 2015, according to  Elsevier SciVal</strong>. 

  Best Paper Award</strong> from International Conference on IoT Technologies for Health Care, 2015. 

  Best Paper</strong> Candidate in 25th IEEE DFT Symposium. 


  Ulla Tuominen</strong> Foundation Research Excellence Award, 2012. 

  Best Student Paper Award</strong> from IEEE International Symposium on Defect and Fault Tolerance in VLSI and Nanotechnology Systems (DFT) Sponsored by  Intel Corporation</strong>, 2011. 
  Nokia</strong> Foundation Research Excellence Award, 2011. 


